@startuml refs-topology
title What a Dolt-backed GitHub repo actually contains

skinparam monochrome false
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
    BorderColor #666
}
skinparam node {
    BackgroundColor #EAF3FF
    BorderColor #0969DA
}
skinparam cloud {
    BackgroundColor #FFF8D6
    BorderColor #C0A02E
}

cloud "github.com/owner/repo.git\n(bare git repo)" as GH {
    rectangle "**refs/heads/main**\n(seed commit)\n\ntree:\n  README.md" as HEADS #D9EDFF
    rectangle "**refs/dolt/data**\n(dolt's private ref)\n\ntree:\n  manifest\n  <chunk>.darc\n  <noms-chunks>" as DOLT #FFE7A8
}

node "GitHub web UI /\nvanilla `git clone`" as BROWSER
node "`dolt clone`" as DOLT_CLONE

BROWSER -[#0969DA]-> HEADS : reads refs/heads/*\nsees: "just a README"
DOLT_CLONE -[#C0A02E]-> DOLT : fetches refs/dolt/data\nreconstructs: full SQL database
DOLT_CLONE -[#C0A02E,dashed]-> HEADS : also sees main\n(the README commit)

note bottom of GH
  Same bytes, same URL, two different realities —
  because GitHub's UI (and `git clone`) only
  follows `refs/heads/*`, not arbitrary refs.
end note

@enduml
